@startuml seq_quiz_flow
title Workshop Quiz Flow — End-to-End Sequence

actor       "Host"          as Host
participant "Host UI\n(host.js)" as HostUI
participant "Backend\n(FastAPI)" as Backend
participant "Local Agent\n(quiz_core.py)" as Agent
participant "Claude API\n(Anthropic)" as Claude
participant "Participant UI\n(participant.js)" as PaxUI
actor       "Participant"   as Pax

== Quiz Generation ==

Host -> HostUI : Click "Generate Quiz"\n(select N minutes)
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/quiz-request\n{minutes: N}
Backend --> HostUI : 200 OK\nbroadcast: quiz_status{requested}
HostUI -> Host : show "Waiting…"

Agent -> Backend : GET /api/quiz-request (poll loop)
Backend --> Agent : {minutes: N}
Agent -> Agent : read last N min\nof transcription
Agent -> Claude : messages API\n(transcript excerpt)
Claude --> Agent : quiz JSON\n{question, options, correct_indices}
Agent -> Backend : POST /api/quiz-preview\n{question, options, multi, correct_indices}
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: quiz_preview
HostUI -> Host : show preview card\n(question + options + AI hints)

== Poll Launch ==

Host -> HostUI : Click "Fire" (optionally after refining)
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/poll\n{question, options, multi, correct_count}
Backend -> Backend : store poll in state\nclear votes
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state{poll, poll_active=false}
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/poll/status {open: true}
Backend -> Backend : snapshot base_scores\nrecord poll_opened_at
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state{poll_active=true}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state{poll, poll_active=true}
PaxUI -> Pax : render poll options\n"Select exactly N answers"

== Voting ==

Pax -> PaxUI : click option(s)
PaxUI -> Backend : WS: {type: vote / multi_vote,\noption_id(s)}
Backend -> Backend : store vote + timestamp
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: vote_update\n{vote_counts, total_votes}
HostUI -> Host : update live bar chart

== Close Poll ==

Host -> HostUI : Click "Close voting"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/poll/status {open: false}
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state{poll_active=false}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state{poll_active=false}
PaxUI -> Pax : show final vote bars\n(% per option)
HostUI -> Host : show final results\n+ "Mark correct" buttons

== Results ==

Host -> HostUI : click correct option(s)\nto mark answers
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/poll/correct\n{correct_ids}
Backend -> Backend : compute scores\n(R−W)/C × speed bonus\nper participant
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: scores{name→pts}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS: result{correct_ids,\nvoted_ids, score}\n(per participant)
HostUI -> Host : highlight correct bars\n+ participant scores
PaxUI -> Pax : show ✅/❌ per option\n+ personal score

@enduml
